        "title" : null,
        "hasTitle" : false,
        "message" : [
          "%md",
          "",
          "# Marketing Campaign Data",
          "",
          "This notebook creates the `CLIENTS`, `CONTACTS`, `PAST_CAMPAIGNS`, and `PROSPECTS`",
          "tables from CSV files in Object Storage, using `DBMS_CLOUD.COPY_DATA`.",
          "",
          "The data is derived from the UCI Bank Marketing dataset: 45,211 clients from a",
          "Portuguese bank's phone campaigns. Target: `subscribed` (term deposit, Y/N, ~11.7% Y).",
          "",
          "**Changes from the original data:** split into separate tables keyed on a new",
          "`client_id`; columns renamed; `day` + `month` combined into `contact_date` with a",
          "synthetic 2025 year; `unknown` values recoded as nulls; target recoded yes/no to Y/N.",
          "`prospects.csv` is our own addition, not part of the original data.",
          "",
          "### Tables",
          "",
          "**`CLIENTS`** (45,211 rows): client attributes. `age`, `job`, `marital`,",
          "`education`, `default_credit`, `balance` (avg yearly, EUR), `housing_loan`,",
          "`personal_loan`.",
          "",
          "**`CONTACTS`** (45,211 rows): current campaign activity, from",
          "`current_campaign_contacts.csv`. `contact_type` (cellular/telephone),",
          "`contact_date`, `duration_seconds`, `contacts_during_campaign`, `subscribed`",
          "(target). Note: `duration_seconds` is only known after the call, so it leaks the",
          "outcome and should be excluded from predictive models.",
          "",
          "**`PAST_CAMPAIGNS`** (45,211 rows): prior campaign history.",
          "`days_from_last_contact` (-1 = never contacted, ~37k rows), `previous_contacts`,",
          "`past_outcomes` (success/failure/other, null when no history).",
          "",
          "**`PROSPECTS`** (100 rows): `client_id` list of 100 prospective customers to be",
          "targeted in the next campaign.",
          "",
          "Copyright (c) 2026 Oracle Corporation",
          "###### [The Universal Permissive License (UPL), Version 1.0](https://oss.oracle.com/licenses/upl/)"
        ],
        "selectedVisualization" : "html",
        "visualizationConfig" : null,
        "hideCode" : true,
        "hideResult" : false,
